cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY 

The paper discusses computational modelling of insect visual systems for motion perception, which involves neural networks and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses computer vision and robotics applications, which suggests the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the second most likely. The paper also mentions the use of these models in robots and vehicles, which falls under the sub-categories cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the methodology of generating different direction and size selectivity in motion perception, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
